                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>Long rectangular crystalline marble plaque. Ends squared, but clearly missing section on left of stone (perhaps due to a later reuse of the block), and roughness of right side perhaps indicates a broken right side. Rear uneven.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.marble" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html">marble</material> <!-- Small piece flaked off on top edge -->
                                    <objectType ana="#object.plaque" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259">plaque</objectType>
                                    <dimensions>
                                        <height unit="cm">19.5</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">38</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">22.5</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition/>
		    </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>Two columns of Greek funerary texts. Right column intact, but left column is almost completely missing. Perhaps a missing epitaph on the right as well. 4 lines of Greek text in each column, text of both columns is roughly in line. The right column has an unusual stepped indentation of the left margin, with each line starting c.1 character further to the right than the last.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                	<damage/>
			</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Letters are neat, evenly spaced, but finely incised on stone. Letters bear simple serifs. Epsilons have arrows in place of cross-bar. Short cross-bar of the theta in column 2, line 3.</p>
